1.title: Opportunity Knocks
1.plot: Home cooks from across the country audition for a spot in the top 12.

2.title: How Do You Take Your Mystery Box?
2.plot: The top 12 face their first Mystery Box Challenge and a budget-inspired elimination challenge sends one of the home cooks packing.

3.title: Building an Appetite
3.plot: The home cooks face their first team challenge as they prepare a hearty meal for 101 hungry Habitat for Humanity volunteers.

4.title: Fast and Epicure-ious
4.plot: The top 10 are given a mere 30 minutes to tackle a mystery box and must create an original recipe featuring fresh ingredients. Then, a fungi-inspired elimination challenge puts an end to one home cook's food dream.

5.title: Barker's Dozen
5.plot: A Team Challenge finds the home cooks tasked with making donuts for dog owners who frequent an off-leash dog park in Toronto. The losing team must face a Pressure Test, resulting in at least one home cook being eliminated.

6.title: Vive La Pressure Test
6.plot: The remaining top 8 home cooks face an intense series of three consecutive French-inspired pressure tests that will reveal their strengths, skills and weaknesses.

7.title: The Magnificent Seven (+1)
7.plot: The home cooks head to an off-site Team Challenge at the McMichael Canadian Art Collection where they must prepare a Group of Seven-inspired meal for the Order of Canada recipients. (Reality).

8.title: Cooking with (Corner) Gas
8.plot: The home cooks are presented with a massive Mystery Box Challenge and must prepare a diner dish inspired by the cast of Corner Gas Animated.

9.title: On the Line of Fire
9.plot: The Top 6 home cooks face a super-charged Restaurant Takeover Team Challenge with the losing team facing an Elimination Challenge.

10.title: Guess Who's Coming to Dinner?
10.plot: The pressure intensifies as former MasterChef Canada winners drop by for a surprise visit.

11.title: Pop-Up Star
11.plot: The remaining three cooks face the first ever Pop-Up Restaurant Challenge.

12.title: Three Courses, One Crown
12.plot: The two remaining cooks compete for the title of MasterChef Canada in the final.

1.title: White Is the New Black
1.plot: In the series premiere of this Canadian version of the reality-cooking series, 50 amateur chefs arrive to prepare food for the judges.

2.title: Chicken Little
2.plot: The chefs are tasked to cook a chicken dish, using only one pan.

3.title: First Kick at the Box
3.plot: The first mystery-box challenge takes place, giving the winner a significant advantage in the elimination challenge.

4.title: The Puck Drops Here
4.plot: The chefs prepare lunch for the Toronto Maple Leafs during the first team challenge. Later, a pasta cook-off ends with an elimination.

5.title: Where's the Beef
5.plot: The chefs are tasked to choose from one of three Canadian ingredients and pair it with beer.

6.title: Edible Art
6.plot: The chefs are tasked to create beautiful and delicious food for an art-gallery event. Later, the losing team is subjected to a baking competition.

7.title: Brains Before Beauty
7.plot: A sentimental mystery-box challenge requires the contestants to return to their roots. The winner is granted an advantage in an Alberta Beef contest.

8.title: Major Steaks
8.plot: A team challenge takes place at Canadian Forces Base Trenton.

9.title: Great Canadian Bake Off
9.plot: A challenge involving the judges' favorite leftovers is featured. Later, the chefs are tasked to create gourmet versions of popular bake-sale items.

10.title: Meals on Wheels
10.plot: A team challenge, focusing on culinary skills and entrepreneurship, takes place at Toronto City Hall. Later, the losing team faces a pressure test.

11.title: Claws Out
11.plot: The remaining chefs participate in a tag-team challenge, involving a tank of lobsters.

12.title: Line of Fire
12.plot: The chefs are tasked to take over a judge's restaurant. Later, the losing team faces a pressure test.

13.title: Family Style
13.plot: The chefs create a dinner menu for a family reunion. Later, they face a particularly difficult challenge during a pressure test.

14.title: Not-Your-Average-Joe
14.plot: The contestants create a meal, for judge Joe Bastianich, using the chef's favorite ingredients.

15.title: And Then There Were 2
15.plot: The first season ends with the Top 2 finalists engaging in a three-course cook-off, in hopes of winning the $100,000 grand prize.

1.title: Fit to Be Tied
1.plot: Season 2 kicks off with home cooks auditioning for a spot in the kitchen.

2.title: Patriotic Pantry
2.plot: The home cooks, who survived the auditions, move on to the next challenge.

3.title: Constant Cravings
3.plot: Chefs prepare an Asian classic in the first Elimination Challenge.

4.title: Juggling Act
4.plot: In the first team challenge, chefs prepare lunch for the cast and crew of Cirque du Soleil.

5.title: Slice of Life
5.plot: Black truffle and artisan pizza are two ingredients used in the challenge.

6.title: One Potato, Two Potato
6.plot: Cooks prepare poutine dishes and compete in a fresh-pasta Pressure Test.

7.title: No Piece of Cake
7.plot: An elimination challenge, featuring a birthday-cake mystery-box, sees cooks combining odd-couple ingredients.

8.title: Wedding on the Waves
8.plot: A wedding is catered, and the team that gets creamed competes in a pastry challenge.

9.title: Good Things in Small Packages
9.plot: The home cooks are surprised with a Mystery Box, and an Elimination Challenge sends one or more cook home.

10.title: Walking on Eggshells
10.plot: Three eliminated chefs receive a chance to cook their way back into the competition.

11.title: Tea for Two
11.plot: The Top 7 do a cook-along Mystery Box with judge Claudio Aprile, and a tag-team challenge to replicate an afternoon-tea tray.

12.title: Fine Dining Under Fire
12.plot: Home cooks engage in the Restaurant Takeover, and a Pressure Test challenges them with a comfort-food dish.

13.title: From Home, with Love
13.plot: Featuring a Mystery Box competition and an Elimination Challenge.

14.title: The Trip to Bountiful
14.plot: An off-site challenge has every chef out for themselves, and a Pressure Test involves chocolate dessert.

15.title: Ring of Fire
15.plot: In the Season 2 finale, two home cooks compete for the $100,000 prize.

imdb.plot outline: Thousands of cooks from across the country apply, but only the Top contenders are asked to audition for the MASTERCHEF CANADA judges. Each participant presents their signature dish in hopes of earning a coveted white apron. Only the most talented and creative home cooks will move forward to the MASTERCHEF CANADA Kitchen. Each week, the MASTERCHEF CANADA Judges inspire the home cooks to grow and evolve, pushing them toward culinary greatness. Internationally-acclaimed chefs and restaurateurs Michael Bonacini (co-owner of the Oliver & Bonacini restaurant empire), Claudio Aprile (chef/owner of the celebrated Origin restaurants) and Alvin Leung (owner of the Michelin-starred Bo Innovation in Hong Kong) are the firm-but-fair mentors who take these amateurs on a journey from home cook to haute cuisine.
imdb.title: MasterChef Canada
plot: Amateur chefs compete in this Canadian version of the reality-cooking series.::anonymous

Thousands of cooks from across the country apply, but only the Top contenders are asked to audition for the MASTERCHEF CANADA judges. Each participant presents their signature dish in hopes of earning a coveted white apron. Only the most talented and creative home cooks will move forward to the MASTERCHEF CANADA Kitchen. Each week, the MASTERCHEF CANADA Judges inspire the home cooks to grow and evolve, pushing them toward culinary greatness. Internationally-acclaimed chefs and restaurateurs Michael Bonacini (co-owner of the Oliver & Bonacini restaurant empire), Claudio Aprile (chef/owner of the celebrated Origin restaurants) and Alvin Leung (owner of the Michelin-starred Bo Innovation in Hong Kong) are the firm-but-fair mentors who take these amateurs on a journey from home cook to haute cuisine.
